SIMPLE: demoiselle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demoiselle
<hw>De`moi`selle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Damsel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A young lady; a damsel; a
lady's maid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The Numidian crane
(<spn>Anthropoides virgo</spn>); -- so called on account of the grace
and symmetry of its form and movements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A beautiful, small dragon fly of
the genus <gen>Agrion</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demolish</ent>⟦br⟧
